aightens to full height, standing above the seated workers. His expression is calm but resolute. A woman seated below him glances up, while others continue at their desks or turn slightly to watch.\n\nThe blond man, now visibly agitated, raises both arms and gestures broadly in front of the office’s tall glowing wall panels. His mouth is open as he speaks, then he leans forward with a tense posture. His expression remains angry, and he continues pacing or shifting his weight as if trying to regain control.\n\nThe setting changes to a warm, busy coffee shop. Sunlight fills the space through large front windows. Brick walls, potted plants, wooden benches, small tables, and seated customers create a relaxed public atmosphere. A woman in a blue sweater and dark pants stands on top of a table or bench near the window, elevated above people seated around her with laptops and drinks. She faces the room, standing straight with her arms at her sides, as if joining the same public declaration. Reversed lettering on the window includes the word “COFFEE,” and the city street is visible outside with buildings and passing pedestrians.\n\nBehind the coffee bar, a young barista with dark hair and bangs looks up from an espresso machine. She wears a white shirt under a teal apron and holds a metal milk pitcher in one hand, pausing mid-task. Stacks of white cups and saucers sit on the counter beside her. Her expression is attentive and slightly puzzled, as if she has noticed the commotion in the café.\n\nThe scene moves to a nighttime city street. Tall buildings with lit windows rise in the background. An ambulance is parked with its rear doors open and red lights glowing. A paramedic or emergency worker in a teal jacket stands on the back step or bumper, elevated above the street. Another person lies on a stretcher behind him at the open ambulance doors. At the bottom of the image, on-screen subtitle text appears, first in Spanish, “Uso Zoom para traducir,” then in English, “I use Zoom to translate,” accompanied by a small Zoom-like blue icon. The emergency worker stands upright and looks outward while the patient remains reclined below him.\n\nA closer view shows the patient, a bald man lying on the stretcher at the ambulance entrance, looking up toward the standing emergency worker. The subtitle “I use Zoom to translate.” remains visible at the bottom.\n\nThe commercial then cuts to a bright blue end card. Centered in large white lowercase letters is the Zoom logo text, “zoom.” Beneath it, in smaller pale text, it reads: “AI-first work platform, Phone, Contact Center, and more.”\n\nFinally, the office scene returns. The blond man is again in the foreground, still pointing forcefully across the room with his arm extended. Behind him, the Black man remains standing on a desk above the cubicles. Other employees sit or watch from around the room. The blond man’s face is tense and animated, as if still resisting the growing movement of workers standing up throughout the office and beyond.",
